latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Did you know we grow more than 17 different varieties of rice? Our nursery team knows each one inside and out and they’re constantly thinking about how to improve them. They study, select, and cross natural, non-GMO varieties for impeccable taste AND compatibility with organic farming practices. It may seem grain-ular, but it’s part of our promise to make better food for the table while leaving a better world for the next generation. 🌾🌎

latestIgtvVideos.title: In the Greenhouse: New Rice from the Grain Up
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Did you know we grow more than 17 different varieties of rice? Our Nursery Team knows each one inside and out and they’re constantly thinking about how to improve them. They study, select, and cross natural, non-GMO varieties for impeccable taste AND compatibility with organic farming practices. It may seem grain-ular, but it means our rice is good from the grain up so we can make better food for the table while leaving a better world for the next generation! 🌾🌎 ⁠ 

#GoodFromTheGrainUp #OrganicFarming #WholeGrainGoodness ⁠

latestIgtvVideos.title: Planting Season
latestIgtvVideos.caption: It’s a bird, it’s a plane, it’s PLANTING SEASON! Did you know we use planes to plant rice? Since rice grows in water, we start by leveling and flooding the fields. Before takeoff, we soak the seed in water to weigh it down. Then we give the seed a chance to breathe while it taxis to the airstrip. This jumpstarts the germination process so when the seed hits the soil, it’s ready to grow! 🛩🌱🌾 #rice101 #goodfromthegrainup #wholegraingoodness

latestIgtvVideos.title: On the Farm with Bryce Lundberg
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Our commitment to conservation runs deep. Each winter, we flood a portion of our fields with water. The fields provide habitat for thousands of birds as they travel the Pacific Flyway. The birds put rice straw in contact with the soil, which helps prep the fields for planting. Once they fly away, we return the water to rivers and streams, where nutrients from the fields support the salmon population. It’s a win-win-win of working in partnership with nature. 🌾🦆🐟🌎 #wholegraingoodness #inpartnershipwithnature #lundbergfamilyfarms

latestIgtvVideos.title: Meet one of our family farmers!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
As a fourth-generation rice grower, Anders has learned to treat the land like another member of the family: with respect, appreciation, and the (more than) occasional conversation about cover crops. 🌾

#wholegraingoodness

✨ We’ve teamed up for a SWEET giveaway! ✨
@LundbergFarms and @AlecsIceCream have joined forces to bring a little joy and calm to New York with our Rice Cream Sandwich pop-up! 🍦🍘 This irresistible treat combines Lundberg’s crunchy whole-grain rice cakes, decadent chocolate, and Alec’s rich, creamy ice cream—pure perfection in every bite.
 
We’ll be sharing these stress-melting delights on June 26-27. Hint: Our location is home to one of NYC’s most iconic landmarks! And for those who can’t join us, we’ll bring the Cake Break to them!
 
Here’s how to send a break to your favorite everyday heroes—nurses, teachers, construction workers, police, and more:
✨ Follow @LundbergFarms + @AlecsIceCream
✨ Tag a New Yorker who works hard and deserves a delicious break.
✨ Share why they’re amazing 💬
 
We’ll pick a group of nominated heroes to receive a delivery of Rice Cream Sandwiches on either 6/26 or 6/27. Because life can feel heavy, but together we’re making it a little lighter—one Rice Cream Sandwich at a time. 🧡
 
Deadline Extended! Giveaway entries now accepted through on Wednesday, June 18th.   
 We’ll choose a winner and send you a DM to notify you. We will need the name and address for the person you’ll want to send a cake break to. We WILL NOT ask for any other personal information, do not be fooled by scammers posing as Lundberg and asking for sensitive personal info.
 
Must be 18+ and a resident of the US. No purchase necessary. Void where prohibited. This giveaway is not sponsored or endorsed by Instagram.
